ave thicker walls","They have smaller diameters","They have more internal valves","They anastomose less frequently","They have fewer smooth muscle cells"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ELymphatic collecting vessels differ from veins in several key structural features. \u003Cstrong\u003EMore internal valves \u003C/strong\u003Eare present in lymphatic collecting vessels compared to veins, occurring approximately every 2-3mm along the vessel. These frequent valves are essential for preventing backflow of lymph and maintaining unidirectional flow against gravity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELymphatic vessels actually have \u003Cstrong\u003Ethinner walls than comparable veins\u003C/strong\u003E, allowing for greater compliance and responsiveness to changes in interstitial fluid pressure. Lymphatic collecting vessels \u003Cstrong\u003Etypically have larger diameters\u003C/strong\u003E than comparable veins, facilitating the transport of larger particles and immune cells. Lymphatic vessels form \u003Cstrong\u003Emore extensive anastomotic networks\u003C/strong\u003E than veins, providing multiple pathways for lymph flow. Lymphatic collecting vessels have a \u003Cstrong\u003Ewell-developed smooth muscle layer \u003C/strong\u003Ethat enables active pumping through rhythmic contractions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Lymphatic collecting vessels have thinner walls, larger diameters, and more frequent anastomoses compared to veins.","Internal valves are more numerous in lymphatic collecting vessels than in veins to prevent backflow of lymph.","Lymphatic vessels have well-developed smooth muscle layers that enable active pumping of lymph."],"references":["Vittet D. Lymphatic collecting vessel maturation and valve morphogenesis. Microvasc Res. 2014 Nov;96:31-7. doi: 10.1016\\/j.mvr.2014.07.001. Epub 2014 Jul 12. PMID: 25020266.","Weber E, Aglian\u000f M, Bertelli E, Gabriele G, Gennaro P, Barone V. Lymphatic Collecting Vessels in Health and Disease: A Review of Histopathological Modifications in Lymphedema. Lymphat Res Biol. 2022 Oct;20(5):468-477. doi: 10.1089\\/lrb.2021.0090. Epub 2022 Jan 17. PMID: 35041535; PMCID: PMC9603277.","Krams, R., \u0026 B\u0000e4ck, M. (Eds.). (2017). The ESC textbook of vascular biology. Oxford University Press."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96089"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14968"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96089","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96089"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-15T00:12:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-15T00:12:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7656"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114074"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4914","links":{"self":"